NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Margaret's comment about not being able to respond to my overcall, having only 4 HCP, is not really relevant here. Let me explain why. In a balancing situation, which this is, the points are approximately evenly spread out/ So even though Margaret has fewer points, if she decides to balance she is bidding on the partnership assets, not just what is in her hand.|
PG| ***** 21 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|In fact, it is better if she is weaker than stronger. I know that sounds odd, but since the points are approximately even between the 2 hands, if she is weaker that means I must be stronger. And that is good for our side, because I have the strong hand behind the stronger opponent's hand (the one who opened). That means more of our finesses are going to work.|
